The best home for modern WordPress sites

Hi Wolf IQ,

It's time to update PHP, as active support of PHP 8.0 ended over a year ago, and security support (patches to address security issues) ended on November 26, 2023.

In May, we'll begin to update any remaining PHP 8.0 sites to PHP 8.1. Here's the schedule:

  • Today, March 26, we are removing the PHP 8.0 option for live sites.
  • Tuesday, April 23: we'll remove the PHP 8.0 option for Standard and Premium staging environments.
  • Tuesday, May 7: we'll begin to update any sites still using PHP 8.0 to PHP 8.1.

We can't give you a specific date or time when we will update your sites, as we expect the update process to take several weeks to complete. To control when your site is updated, you can update your site's PHP version before May 7.

How to update to the latest version of PHP

Updating PHP versions in MyKinsta can be done with a couple of clicks. "Minor version" updates like 8.0 to 8.1 don't usually introduce changes that could break any functions on your site. But before you change the PHP version for your live site, do some testing to be sure. Our safe PHP upgrades guide takes you through the process.

Pro tip: If your WordPress version is up to date, PHP version incompatibilities are most likely to be found in themes or plugins.

What you stand to gain from a PHP update

More recent versions of PHP are not only safer, but they're also usually faster than the versions they replace. Read our PHP Benchmarks article for a performance comparison between PHP 8.1, 8.2, and 8.3.

Learn about other benefits of updating in our articles, What's New in PHP 8.1, What's New in PHP 8.2, and PHP 8.3: What's New and What's Changed.

We're here to help

Everyone at Kinsta is dedicated to providing you with the fastest, safest, and most secure website hosting environment anywhere. We know that technology updates can be inconvenient and disruptive. But occasional updates are necessary to maintain the safety and performance you've come to expect.

We're here for you if you have questions about the PHP version changes. Feel free to connect with us in MyKinsta.
